  "texts": [
    "To normalize the results to the desired range of 0 to 1, all the resulting numbers from both the GA and RL approaches are divided by 3.",
    "This normalization method ensures that the different scales of the numbers do not disproportionately affect the diversity calculation, allowing for a fair and consistent comparison.",
    "In the 6-DOF case study, for both the GA and RL approaches, the chromosomes for GA and states for RL consist of six inputs, representing the joint angles.",
    "Each input is divided by the joint's torque limit to ensure the magnitudes fall within the range of 0 to 1.",
    "This standardization ensures that input values are dimensionless and comparable, regardless of the joint's specific torque limits, thereby facilitating reliable and meaningful comparisons and calculations."
  ],
